---

<BaseLayout
  title="Commercial Solar Systems Geelong | Business Solar Installation | EES"
  description="Commercial solar panel installation for businesses in Geelong and regional Victoria. Reduce overheads and meet sustainability goals."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Commercial Solar Systems</h1>
      <p>Reduce your operating costs with solar designed for your business.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Solar for Business</h2>
      <p>
        Commercial electricity rates are high and rising. A well-designed solar system offsets a significant portion of your daytime energy consumption — the hours when most businesses are running at full capacity and electricity costs the most.
      </p>
      <p>
        Unlike residential systems, commercial solar is designed around your business's load profile, roof or ground-mount availability, and operational hours. We design systems that maximise self-consumption, not just generation.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Design and Install</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Rooftop systems</strong> — from 10 kW to 100+ kW, designed for flat or pitched commercial roofs</li>
        <li><strong>Ground-mount systems</strong> — for properties with available land and unsuitable roofs</li>
        <li><strong>Three-phase systems</strong> — for commercial and industrial electrical configurations</li>
        <li><strong>Monitoring and reporting</strong> — real-time performance data for energy management and reporting</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Financial Benefits</h2>
      <p>
        Commercial solar offers strong returns:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Reduced electricity bills</strong> — offset daytime energy consumption directly</li>
        <li><strong>Federal STC rebate</strong> — applied as a point-of-sale discount, reducing upfront cost</li>
        <li><strong>Tax depreciation</strong> — commercial solar systems can be depreciated as a business asset</li>
        <li><strong>Sustainability credentials</strong> — meet reporting requirements and demonstrate environmental commitment</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our Process</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Site assessment</strong> — we evaluate your property, energy usage, and electrical infrastructure</li>
        <li><strong>System design</strong> — engineered for your specific load profile and roof</li>
        <li><strong>Approvals</strong> — we handle grid connection applications, permits, and rebate paperwork</li>
        <li><strong>Installation</strong> — scheduled around your operations to minimise disruption</li>
        <li><strong>Commissioning</strong> — full testing, monitoring setup, and handover</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Add Battery Storage</h2>
      <p>
        Solar and battery together can further reduce your electricity costs by storing excess generation for use during peak tariff periods and reducing demand charges. See our <a href="/services/commercial/battery-systems">commercial battery systems</a> page for more detail.
      </p>

      <p>
        <a href="/services/consultation">Book a free consultation</a> to get a commercial solar assessment for your business.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <ScrollIndicator />
</BaseLayout>
